modules.description: Pings an InfluxDB host and writes a list of time-series points to a specified database. Operates with strings, integers, and Influxdb.Point.t structures. Used to monitor server availability and submit telemetry data asynchronously.

Handles writing and querying InfluxDB databases using Lwt for asynchronous I/O. Operates on time-series data structures, including points and queries, with support for tag sets and field mappings. Enables real-time data ingestion and ad-hoc metric retrieval in event-driven applications.

Provides asynchronous communication with an InfluxDB host, enabling the submission of time-series data and server health checks. Accepts strings, integers, and point structures to format and send data to a database. Supports monitoring server availability by pinging the host and writing telemetry metrics. Examples include tracking system uptime and logging sensor readings in real time.
